defaultLarger Families and the overall Benefit CapdefaultUnder the 
defaultBenefit C
defaultap, unless they are exempt, families with 
defaultsix
default or more children receive only 50p Housing
default Benefit. Whilst boroughs are working with households to help them get into employment, for single parents with young children, child care costs in 
defaultLondon
default make this very difficult. If the children are at school, part-time employment with hours that fit in 
defaultwith schools or self-employment may be the only options. If the parent is unable to get work, then they may be moved to a cheaper area. However, there are often reasons why this cannot happen. For example, it is difficult to move families with a child doin
defaultg GSCEs or A-levels because of the disruption to a key stage of their education.  
