defaultLocal authorities are in a difficult position in estimating the effects of direct payments, based on the roll out progress of Universal Credit. The majority are expecting losses and making bad debt provision, particularly in the light of the pilot authorit
defaulties who suffered significant decreases in rental income. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultThere are potential difficulties in ensuring payment of UC for TA cases in bed and breakfast placements for a few nights due to UC being assessed monthly, based on the claimant’s circumstances at 
defaultthe end of the month. If B&amp;B claimants do not make a UC claim when they enter B&amp;B they (or more likely the local authority) will not receive any payment towards the rent. Direct payments for 
defaulttemporary 
defaultaccommodation
default placements
default would be welcome.
default 
